from the sons of Joseph: 
from Ephraim, Elishama son of Ammihud, 
and from Manasseh, Gamaliel son of Pedahzur;

Whenever the ark set out, Moses would say, 
“Rise up, O LORD! May Your enemies be scattered; 
may those who hate You flee before You.”

He said, “Hear now My words: 
If there is a prophet among you, I, the LORD, will reveal Myself to him in a vision; 
I will speak to him in a dream.

I speak with him face to face, clearly and not in riddles; 
he sees the form of the LORD. 
Why then were you unafraid to speak against My servant Moses?”
